notesStmt.note: Title from margin abbreviation throughout, upper left verso.
532 leaves foliated 1-59, upper left and lower right verso; 60-117, upper left verso; 118-267, upper left and lower right verso; 268-532, upper left verso.

Mistakes covered over in white or blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout; vertical margins marked with double black line; the final folio (f. 532) and colophon are badly damaged.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Compendium of Indian medical knowledge up until the 17th century including details of medical drugs, as well as diagnoses and treatments for many medical conditions including a variety of fevers, loss of appetite and indigestion, piles, bronchitis, hiccups, epilepsy, diabetes, etc. There is intermittent commentary (ṭīkā) at various points throughout the text.
